Durban - Five men, aged between 18 and 39, appeared in court for an incident that claimed the life of a man in Nsuze last week. A second person was left seriously wounded. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said the five men appeared in the Nsuze Magistrate's Court on charges of murder and attempted murder. She said the five are accused of assaulted 28-year-old Siyabonga Mthembu and his friend, aged 23, who were on their way home. The group assaulted the two with bush knives and wooden sticks. The victims attempted to run away however, they were caught at the nearby homestead and the ordeal continued," she said. Mbele said Mthembu succumbed to his injuries while the younger man was rushed to hospital. "On Tuesday, police arrested Phumlani James Makhanya, 28, Siboniso Hlongwa 22, and 18-year-old Sifundo Ndlela. Sphamandla “Ziqabulele” Nzama, 39 and Phila Mzobe, 18, were arrested. All five accused were remanded into custody until their next court appearance," she said. It is alleged that the deceased were falsely accused of a theft although no criminal case was reported to the police in the area. Daily News